Unorg. Fed. Terr. (1786-09-14)

1786/09/14 -> 1787/07/12

The U.S. accepted Connecticut's cession of lands north and west of Pennsylvania and the Ohio River, except for a tract (Western Reserve) lying north of 41 degrees north latitude (Connecticut's southern line) and extending 120 miles west of Pennsylvania.

(Terr. Papers U.S., 2:24 n. 62)
